0 2HELP ANSI0

  ANSI can be turned on and off with the '~' key or in the .EC enter
configuration menu.  If your terminal does not support ANSI this will
cause extra characters to be displayed, at least. What it will do is make
room prompts inverse, message headers bold and let you see different colors
in the messages where users have inserted TurboCit's special ESC sequences.
  The Escape sequence starts with a CTRL-A and then a number (0-4) or a
letter (a-h or A-H).  These are converted to the ANSI equivalent when the
code is sent over the modem.

 What it does:                 What it looks like:
 ^A0 -- NORMAL                 0Normal0
 ^A1 -- BLINK                  1Blinking0
 ^A2 -- REVERSE (inverse)      2Inverted0
 ^A3 -- BOLD (highlight)       3Boldface0
 ^A4 -- UNDERLINE              4Underline0

